# API Endpoint Structure

- Use response_model for type safety 
- Use appropriate HTTP status codes (201 for POST, 204 for DELETE)
- Use Depends(get_async_session) for database sessions 
- Use Query() with validation contraints (ge, le, min_length)
- Let Pydantic schemas handle validation automatically 

# Service Layer 
- Accept AsyncSession in __init__
- Use verb prefixes: get_, create_, update_, delete_, list_
- Raise custom exceptions from app.core.exceptions 
- Return domain models, not response schemas 
- Keep all business logic in services, not endpoints 

# Error Handling 
- Use NotFoundError -> 404, Unauthorized -> 401, ForbiddenError -> 403, ValidationError -> 422
- In Services: Raise exceptions, don't catch them 
- In Endpoints: Let exceptions bubble to FastAPI handlers 
- Log expected errors as warnings, unexpected as erros 